On the contrary, to accept a malonyl group, arginine residues contribute to the stabilization of the malonyl group via hydrogen bonds in Dm3MAT3 and NtMAT1, although these enzymes applied Arg at different positions: Arg 178 in Dm3MAT3 and Arg 39 in NtMAT1. These Arg positions correspond to Phe182 and Ser45, respectively, in Gt5,3 ′ AT ( Table 1 ). It has been reported that the three residue mutants of malonyl transferase from
Salvia splendens Sellow ex Nees (Lamiaceae)
(Ss5MaT1) exhibited a change in ligand specificity to aromatic acyl-CoA (
). The mutation was engineered at Val39-Arg40-Arg41 of Ss5MaT1 to Met-Leu-Gln. Considering these results, the two positions (positions 45 and 182) in Gt5,3 ′ AT are likely to be critical for acyl-CoA recognition specificity. Supplementary Figure S1 shows the sequence alignment among the characterized flavonoid BAHD ATs (
). For malonyl-CoA ATs, it is important to include Arg either at position 45 or position 182, except for two malonyl-CoA ATs, Ss5MaT2 and MaT5. However, Ss5MaT2 includes Val at position 179 and Asp at position 401, and MaT5 includes Trp at position 401. These positions in other flavonoid BAHD ATs are occupied with Ala/Gly and Gly/Ser at positions 179 and 401, respectively (Supplementary Figure S1 ). These two positions correspond to the side wall of the acyl-CoA binding site ( Fig. 3A ). Bulky amino acids in these positions make the binding site narrower, thus inhibiting aromatic acyl-CoA binding.

Crystallization was performed using the sitting-drop vapor-diffusion method at 293 K. The drops were composed of 1.0 μL of protein solution and 0.3–0.7 μL of reservoir solution. The crystals of Gt5,3 ′ AT and truncated Gt5,3 ′ AT were grown in 0.1 M HEPES buffer (pH 7.5) with 1.1–1.4 M sodium citrate. The crystals of the truncated Gt5,3 ′ AT were soaked in 1 mM caffeoyl-CoA and 1 mM delphinidin 3,5-diglucoside overnight at 293 K. Data collection was carried out at 100 K with 5% glycerol as a cryoprotectant. The crystal data of Gt5,3 ′ AT and truncated Gt5,3 ′ AT were collected at BL17 A at the Photon Factory (Tsukuba, Japan ) and using beamline X10SA (Swiss Light Source, Villigen, Switzerland ), respectively. The diffraction data of Gt5,3 ′ AT were processed and scaled using the HKL2000 program package (
). The diffraction data of the truncated Gt5,3 ′ AT were processed using the XDS program package (
) and scaled with the CCP4 program suite (
).

