To investigate the positional selectivity of anthocyanin 3,5,3 ′ -triglucoside for Gt5,3 ′ AT , docking simulation using the Glide program (
;
) was performed to predict its binding mode. For the docking preparation, anthocyanin 3,5,3 ′ -triglucoside was ionized at pH 7.0 ± 2.0 by Epik implemented in Ligprep. The crystal structure of Gt5,3 ′ AT was ionized at pH 7.0, and the hydrogen atoms were optimized by the OPLS3e force field using Protein Preparation Wizard. The receptor grid was then generated with a scaling factor of 1.0. Using the Glide SP mode with expanded sampling option, 202 docking poses were obtained. Considering the accessibility of the 5 or 3 ′ glucose moiety to the catalytic site, 10 docking poses of which either the hydroxyl oxygen in the 5 or 3 ′ glucose moiety came closest to the linker carbon atom of caffeoyl-CoA among all the ligand atoms and positioned within 6 Å were selected to assess the positional selectivity.
